$ Bash: if

`if` evaluates a commands (`CMD`) → Linux/shell/bash/parameters/special/exit-status[exit status ($?)]. An exit status of 0 is considered true, all other status
are considered false.

code {
if CMD; then
   ...
   ...
fi
code }

code {
if CMD; then
   ...
   ...
else
   ...
   ...
fi
code }

code {
if CMD; then
   ...
   ...
elif CMD2; then
   ...
   ...
else
   ...
   ...
fi
code }

CMD might be a → Linux/shell/commands/square-bracket[square bracket command].

sa:

  → Linux/shell/bash/

  → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/about-Bash/tree/master/conditional-constructs
